notes_display: In Historical Sketches of the Paper Currency of the American Colonies by Henry Phillips, Jr. (1865). Given to Dr. Jesse C. Green in 1890. Leaf 56BM.
issue_place_s: Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, United States of America
issue_obverse_legend_s: Nine Pence. THIS Bill shall pass current for Nine Pence, according to an Act of General Assembly, of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania, passed the 7th day of April, in the year 1781. Dated the 20th day of April, 1781. NINE PENCE.
issue_reverse_legend_s: To Counterfeit is DEATH. | NINE PENCE. PHILADELPHIA, Printed by John Dunlap. 1781. | NEW BILL.
